(thirdQuint)An Open Label Trial of Duloxetine in the Treatment of Irritable Bowel Syndrome and Comorbid Generalized Anxiety Disorder.

 Generalized Anxiety Disorder (GAD) is commonly associated with Irritable Bowel Syndrome(IBS).

 The etiology of IBS remains unknown and it is often refractory to treatment.

 Duloxetine has demonstrated efficacy in the treatment of GAD as well as other pain disorders including fibromyalgia and diabetic neuropathy.

 We plan to study 30 subjects with diagnoses of IBS and GAD between the ages of 18 and 65 years.

 There will be a single-blind placebo-run-in for the first 2 weeks, followed by open-label duloxetine for 12 weeks flexibly titrated to 120 mg/day.

 Subjects will be informed that they will receive placebo for 2 weeks during the trial.

 All study visits will be at Allegheny General Hospital Department of Psychiatry.

 The study consists of a total of nine office visits.

